{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588849"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:11:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:11:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15177"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15177","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15177"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.27,0.05,0.41,0.24,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7868"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65636"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7868","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7868"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15177"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51075"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6904"},{"type":"tags","id":"7415"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"8138"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19177"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19180"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21851"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65636","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65636"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the relative frequency of different types of abdominal wall hernias is important for clinical practice. Apart from an appreciation of the anatomy, a clear physical examination of many of today\u0027s patients (Image) can be challenging. The old medical adage of \u0027common things occur commonly\u0027 should always be remembered when trying to make a diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the commonest type of abdominal wall hernia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Direct inguinal","Femoral","Indirect inguinal","Para-umbilical","Spigelian"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESo-called \u0027naturally occurring\u0027 abdominal wall hernias account for about 90% of all hernias, with incisional hernias making up the remaining 10%. The distribution pattern is approximately:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIndirect\u003C/strong\u003E inguinal hernias 50% (Image 1)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect\u003C/strong\u003E inguinal hernias 25% (Image 2)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFemoral\u003C/strong\u003E  10% (Image 3)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPara-umbilical\u003C/strong\u003E 7% (Image 4)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEpigastric\u003C/strong\u003E 5% (Image 5)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are other, less common hernias (eg spigelian) which contribute to less than 5% of the total. This pattern reflects the anatomical vulnerabilities of the abdominal wall, with the inguinal canal being particularly susceptible to herniation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Indirect inguinal hernias account for approximately 50% of all abdominal wall hernias."],"references":["Hammoud M, Gerken J. Inguinal Hernia. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK513332/","Conze J, Klinge U, Schumpelick V. Hernias. In: Holzheimer RG, Mannick JA, editors. Surgical Treatment: Evidence-Based and Problem-Oriented. Munich: Zuckschwerdt; 2001. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK6888/","Aiolfi A, Cavalli M, Ferraro SD, Manfredini L, Bonitta G, Bruni PG, Bona D, Campanelli G. Treatment of Inguinal Hernia: Systematic Review and Updated Network Meta-analysis of Randomized Controlled Trials. Ann Surg. 2021 Dec 1;274(6):954-961. doi: 10.1097/SLA.0000000000004735. PMID: 33427757.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51075"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15177"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21243"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21244"},{"type":"media","id":"21245"},{"type":"media","id":"21246"},{"type":"media","id":"21247"},{"type":"media","id":"21248"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21243","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21243"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5SQPd19zxe3LEVbDkJf7my7AwcNEDl.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5SQPd19zxe3LEVbDkJf7my7AwcNEDl.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1125}},{"type":"media","id":"21244","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21244"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/zsKkneeX78iurNEFIHRdVVnOhT5FDj.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/zsKkneeX78iurNEFIHRdVVnOhT5FDj.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":292,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"21245","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21245"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/bHZJbMEnFMP5GOakUlHy9N1Fz8uav0.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/